---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = "About Me";
const description = "Learn more about the developer behind The Calm Developer blog.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
	<article class="prose">
		<header>
			<h1>About Me</h1>
		</header>

		<section>
			<p>
				Hello! I'm Harrison, a software engineer focused on building reliable, well-structured systems
				and continuously improving my understanding of how software works under the hood.
			</p>
			<p>
				I work primarily with C nowadays, but started my career in modern web technologies such
				as a Typescript and React Frontend specialist. I am focused on always being better and learning
				more.
			</p>
			<p>
				I'm especially interested in learning more about memory and performance. I want to understand the
				why and how and not just "sling code". Through this blog I hope to share what I am learning
				and I hope to break down complex systems using AI to jumpstart my learning.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>My Expertise</h2>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Systems & Low-Level Programming:</strong> C programming, memory management,
				and performance-thinking</li>
				<li><strong>Frontend Development:</strong> React, Typescript, and SCSS.</li>
				<li><strong>Software Architecture:</strong> Designing scalable and maintainable systems.</li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>Philosophy</h2>
			<p>
				I believe in being "the calm developer": writing code that is easy to read, simple to maintain,
				and focused on solving real problems without unnecessary complexity. Great software isn't just about
				the features—it's about the craftsmanship and the long-term health of the codebase.
			</p>
			<p>
				For me, becoming a better engineer means diving deeper and understanding more. Understand the machine.
				Understand the principles. And trust in your hard work.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>Connect With Me</h2>
			<p>
				I'm always open to discussing new projects, interesting technologies, or just chatting about
				software development in general.
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li><a href="https://github.com/hstephan23">GitHub</a></li>
				<li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/harrison-stephan-software-engineer/">LinkedIn</a></li>
				<li><a href="mailto:thecalmdeveloper@gmail.com">Email Me</a></li>
			</ul>
		</section>
	</article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
	section {
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
	}

	h2 {
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
		padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
		margin-top: 3rem;
	}

	ul {
		list-style-type: none;
		padding-left: 0;
	}

	ul li {
		margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
		position: relative;
		padding-left: 1.5rem;
	}

	ul li::before {
		content: "→";
		position: absolute;
		left: 0;
		color: var(--link);
	}
</style>
